  "prompt": "PLAN-GATE PROTOCOL ACTIVE. Real-money urgency: 9 open Coinbase positions are unprotected at the venue right now. Operator is awake and watching.\n\nANTI-TRUNCATION + CHECKPOINT RULES (do not skip):\n\n1. For any file >500 lines, use the Write tool (full overwrite), NOT the Edit tool. Edit-tool truncation hazard documented in advisor brief §2.1. Phase 4's session truncated 8 unrelated files via Edit; do not repeat.\n2. After every file modification: `wc -l <file>`, `git diff --stat -- <file>`, and `python -c \"import ast; ast.parse(open('<file>').read())\"`. If wc -l drops by more than your edit added: STOP, `git checkout HEAD -- <file>`, switch to Write.\n3. SCOPE DISCIPLINE: only modify files explicitly listed in your plan's section (a). Crypto-side only. NO options, NO equity entry, NO unrelated services.\n4. CHECKPOINT DISCIPLINE: after every meaningful piece of work, do an interim git commit with message starting `wip(coinbase-bracket):`. Final commit can squash.\n\nSTEP 1 -- READ in this exact order:\n  - CLAUDE.md\n  - docs/STRATEGY/PROTOCOL.md\n  - docs/STRATEGY/COWORK_ADVISOR_BRIEF.md (focus §2 hazards, §5 currently-armed state)\n  - docs/STRATEGY/NEXT_TASK.md\n  - docs/STRATEGY/QUEUED/f-coinbase-bracket-coverage-fix.md (the brief)\n  - app/services/trading/stop_engine.py lines 685-740 and 920-960\n  - app/services/trading/bracket_intent_writer.py upsert_bracket_intent + idempotency notes\n  - app/services/trading/bracket_reconciliation_service.py missing_stop branch\n  - app/services/trading/bracket_writer_g2.py place_missing_stop function\n  - app/services/trading/auto_trader.py fill-handler that sets trade.stop_loss\n\nSTEP 2 -- PLAN. Write your plan to scripts/_claude_session_consult/$env:CHILI_SESSION_ID/plan.request.md. Cover ALL sections (a) through (g) from the brief. Be specific. Per-file `wc -l` documented.\n\nSTEP 3 -- WAIT for plan.response.md. Poll every 30s, up to 2h.\n\nSTEP 4 -- READ THE RESPONSE. APPROVED / REVISE / ABORT per protocol.\n\nSTEP 5 -- AFTER APPROVED. Implement following the rules above. wip-commit after each meaningful piece. Run pytest for tests/test_coinbase_bracket_coverage.py. Operator will force-recreate manually after CC pushes -- do not attempt force-recreate yourself; CC's docker access may be restricted.\n\nSTEP 6 -- WRITE CC_REPORT. Cover: what bugs were found at code level (with file:line refs), what was fixed, what tests pass, what verification queries should look like post-deploy, what the operator's hot-fix SQL for ACS-USD #1842 should look like. Update NEXT_TASK to STATUS: DONE.\n\nHARD CONSTRAINTS:\n  - Crypto-side only. NO options entry, NO equity entry, NO non-crypto exit code.\n  - Coinbase Phase 6 LIVE soak active. Do NOT disable existing gates (auth flag, cap flag, side check, post-place verify). Phase 4's _SUPPORTED_VENUES = {robinhood, coinbase} is a green light to USE the new path, not bypass it.\n  - No magic-fallback values. None/NULL propagate; gate explicitly.\n  - Edit-tool truncation discipline.",
